{
  "stem": "7506.5",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--St.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Nicholas, as I've told you, its 5 of December every year.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES] So on the 4 of December, as a pure coincidence, is the day before St.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Nicholas, obviously.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And as children, even in the camp, we were looking forward to Sinterklaas.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That's how Dutch children say 'St.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Nicholas,' Sinterklaas.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES] On the 4 of December, apparently all the diamond transport men met in one barrack and made some decision which had tremendous consequences to all of us, which I did not know what those decisions were at that time.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I do know that very soon after the meeting where all the men attended, all the men were put on transport.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES] All the men that had been at the meeting, all diamond workers, all to do with the diamond business, were put on transport.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES] I have now in my possession the original German lists, copies, photocopies, of the original German transport list.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES] The men were ail sent out of Belsen.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I, my mother, nor my sister, or any of the children, or their mothers, for the most part-- with an exception of about three men-- never saw our fathers, or the women their husbands, again.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Ever.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES] The following day, that was the 5th of December, on the day of St.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Nicholas, all the women and older children were taken out of where we were, that part, i.e., the Sternlager, to another part of the camp.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "[PAUSES] It was a bright day that day, I remember.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Cold, but a bright day.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we were all standing, and all of a sudden, the children were told to go to a separate place, a distance, I would say, of no more, maybe, that 30 yards away from the mothers.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
